"'''Missed Chance'''" is a short story by [[Michael A. Stackpole]]. It was originally printed in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 7|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 7]] which was published by [[West End Games]] in [[August]] [[1995]] and was later reprinted in the short story anthology ''[[Tales from the Empire]]'' published by [[Bantam Spectra]] in [[November]] [[1997]]. It was also made available online at [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]].

The story takes place shortly before the novel ''[[X-Wing: Rogue Squadron]]''.

==Plot summary==
Spirited [[Garqi Agricultural University|university]] students are mistaken for full-fledged seditionists by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] government of [[Garqi/Legends|Garqi]], prompting the [[Prison/Legends|arrest]] and interrogation of innocent [[Dynba Tesc]]. Fueling the Imperial crackdown are witness' accounts of a lone [[X-wing starfighter|X-Wing]] flying the night skies – the rash actions of [[Corran Horn/Legends|Corran Horn]], former [[Corporate Sector/Legends|CorSec]] [[Agent/Legends|agent]] on the run from the Empire, who is supposed to keep a low profile. [[Imperial Prefect|Prefect]] [[Mosh Barris/Legends|Mosh Barris]] is determined to impress a visiting [[Imperial Intelligence/Legends|Imperial Intelligence]] [[Officer/Legends|officer]] with his hard line actions against the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebels]]. Advised by his aid Eamon Yzalli, Barris creates a larger trap for the Rebels by allowing Dynba to [[Great Evacuation|escape]] and arrange the freedom of other captive suspects. But when it comes time to spring his trap and round up all the would-be Rebels, Barris finds that Eamon has worked against him to ensure their safe passage. Eamon was, in truth, Corran Horn in disguise. Having fled Garqi, Corran is determined to join the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] as a [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]].

==Continuity==
This story shared an issue of the [[Star Wars Adventure Journal|''Adventure Journal'']] with [[Timothy Zahn|Timothy Zahn]]'s "[[Mist Encounter]]". [[Imperial Prefect|Prefect]] [[Mosh Barris/Legends|Mosh Barris]] was the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Colonel/Legends|Colonel]] whom [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]] ran in circles in Zahn's story, and he was still nursing his wounded pride in [[Michael A. Stackpole|Stackpole]]'s tale, set a quarter [[Standard century/Legends|century]] later.<ref name="TERC" />

